=====Usage notes=====
* In standard English, one is "able '''to''' do something". In some older texts representing various dialects, particularly Irish English, or black speech, "able '''for''' do something" is found instead, and in some Caribbean dialects "able '''with'''" is sometimes found.<ref>{{R:EDD|able}}</ref><ref>Richard Allsopp, Jeannette Allsopp, ''Dictionary of Caribbean English Usage'' (2003), entry "able"</ref>

